Interface ParameterizedCondition<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the parameter of the condition
    All Superinterfaces:
    ModelElement
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ParameterizedCondition<T>
extends ModelElement
    A functional interface to implement parameterized conditions in the action language.

    Represents: condition

    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.

    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ModelBool check(T param)
      The sole method of ParameterizedCondition.

    • Method Detail

      • check

        ModelBool check(T param)
        The sole method of ParameterizedCondition. Override this method to implement the desired condition.

        Overriding methods may not return a null value.

        Overriding methods may only contain a condition evaluation. See the documentation of Model for details about condition evaluations in the model.

        Parameters:
        param - the parameter of the condition
        Returns:
        a ModelBool representing true if the condition holds, a ModelBool representing false otherwise
